<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="convenient-adj">convenient <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kən'viːniənt/    美 /kən'viːniənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-it-is-convenient-for-sb-to-do-sth">1.★ <strong>便利的；方便的：it is convenient (for sb) to do sth:</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is very <strong>convenient to</strong> travel in London by underground.
在伦敦乘坐地铁出游很方便。</p><footer>2011 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If it’s <strong>convenient for</strong> you, let’s meet at 8:30 outside the school gate.
如果你方便的话，我们8点半在学校门口碰面吧。</p><footer>2016 全国书面表达</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>就近的；近便的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a restaurant <strong>convenient for</strong> shops and theatres
靠近商店和剧院的餐馆</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The secretary arranged a(n) <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (方便的) time and place for the applicants to have an interview.  （2012 天津改）  </li>
<li>Would it  <strong><em>_</em></strong>_(对…方便) you to pick me up at four o’clock and take me to the airport?  （2008 山东改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. convenient  2.  be convenient for  </p></div>